cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the characterization of primary traffic in wireless networks and its impact on secondary transmissions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the modeling of idle time distributions, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the security implications of secondary transmissions, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of secondary transmission strategies, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.PF (Performance).
